      • downloadHunt

        public Single<Hunt> downloadHunt(String token,
                                 UUID huntId)
        This method chains multiple operations to add a Hunt record to the local database: 1. A Hunt is requested by ScavengrService. 2. The name of the User who created the hunt is added to the Hunt object. 3. The Hunt is saved to the ScavengrDatabase, which generates a local Long id that replaces the server's UUID as the Primary Key. 4. That id is attached to the Hunt and each of its Clues. 5. The list of Clues is saved to the Database, and each has its unique local Long id attached.
        Parameters:
        token - from Oauth service, used to check User privileges
        huntId - identifies the Hunt to be downloaded.
        Returns:
        the Hunt, modified from the server for the local database.
